**Decommission Steps (to be executed):**  
1. Verify backup integrity: `ls -la /home/user/bind_backup`  
2. Confirm no critical services depend on this server: Check `/etc/resolv.conf` on key hosts.  
3. Run purge command: `sudo apt purge bind9`  
4. Remove residual config files: `sudo rm -rf /etc/bind` (if not already backed up).  
5. Update firewall rules to block DNS traffic to 192.168.1.10.  
6. Log completion in IT change management ticket #CHG-2025-0410.

**Note:** The purge command will remove Bind9 binaries and configuration. The backup at `/home/user/bind_backup` is the sole fallback. Ensure no other processes reference the old server before proceeding.